            "image": "shopify://shop_images/nobl_rims_563198d6-a179-4307-80ca-3a34623f068e.png",
            "caption": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2><strong>24-Hole Rim:</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Weight:</strong> Typically lighter due to fewer spokes and less material used.</li><li><strong>Aerodynamics:</strong> Potential for improved aerodynamics due to fewer spokes disrupting airflow.</li><li><strong>Strength:</strong> Not as strong as higher spoke count rims, suitable for lighter riders or smoother terrain.</li><li><strong>Weight Limitation:</strong> Might not be ideal for heavy riders or rough terrain due to the reduced spoke count's impact on weight distribution.</li></ul>",
            "button_label": "",
            "button_link": ""
          }
        },
        "template--21646610071859__da5af781-417a-41ae-afa4-4511aeaeab62-row-2": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/sc_rims.png",
            "caption": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2><strong>28-Hole Rim:</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Balanced Strength and Weight:</strong> Strikes a balance between weight savings and strength.</li><li><strong>Versatility:</strong> Suitable for a broad range of riders and riding conditions, offering decent strength without excessive weight.</li><li><strong>Usage:</strong> Common on road bikes, some lightweight mountain bike setups, and versatile for various riding styles.</li></ul>",
            "button_label": "",
            "button_link": ""
          }
        },
        "template--21646610071859__da5af781-417a-41ae-afa4-4511aeaeab62-row-3": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/weareone_rims.png",
            "caption": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2><strong>32-Hole Rim:</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Durability:</strong> Offers increased strength and durability due to more spokes distributing the load.</li><li><strong>Stability:</strong> Provides better stability and robustness, suitable for heavier riders or rougher terrain.</li><li><strong>Versatility:</strong> Works well for all-around riding, touring, bikepacking, or mountain biking, especially in challenging conditions.</li></ul>",
            "button_label": "",
            "button_link": ""
          }
        }
      },
