          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h2><strong>Benefits:</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>24-Hole:</strong> Ideal for weight-conscious riders and racing where weight savings are crucial.</li><li><strong>28-Hole:</strong> A good balance between weight and strength, suitable for diverse riding styles.</li><li><strong>32-Hole:</strong> Provides robustness and reliability, catering to heavier riders and rougher terrain where strength is prioritized over weight.</li></ul><p>The choice between these spoke counts depends on factors like rider weight, riding style, terrain, and personal preference for weight savings versus durability. Heavier riders or those riding in demanding conditions might benefit from the durability and strength of 32-hole rims, while lighter riders might appreciate the weight savings of 24-hole rims.</p>"
